    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — discerning Isaiah's intent within the theological and historical context of eighth-century Judah while tracing the canonical lines that reach into the New Testament. The four movements below follow the chapter's own argument structure: structural collapse, theological indictment, courtroom confrontation, and the reversal of pride. Where the Hebrew sharpens the English, a brief lexical note follows.",
